    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAfter `redrawstatus!` is called and a floating window is created, relative to a window that's not the topleft window, the position information is not accurate immediately after.\r\n(the problem does not occur if the floating window is created relative to the topleft window)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n```\r\n\r\nCreate and `:source` the following script:\r\n```vim\r\nsplit\r\nresize 5\r\nredrawstatus!\r\nlet buf = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\nlet opts = {\r\n      \\   'relative': 'win',\r\n      \\   'win': win_getid(2),\r\n      \\   'width': 30,\r\n      \\   'height': 2,\r\n      \\   'col': 50,\r\n      \\   'row': 0,\r\n      \\   'style': 'minimal'\r\n      \\ }\r\nlet win = nvim_open_win(buf, 0, opts)\r\nechom nvim_win_get_position(win)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat script splits the editor into two windows, resizes the top window to have a height of 5, redraws that status line, then creates a new floating window. The reported position immediately after creating is not correct, as echo'd:\r\n```\r\n[12, 50]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `resize 5` command is not necessary to reproduce the issue, but makes it easier to figure out the expected line that should be reported.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the position information to be:\r\n```\r\n[6, 50]\r\n```\r\nwhich is what's shown if `echom nvim_win_get_position(win)` is ran _after_ the script.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nKubuntu 23.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKonsole 22.12.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage",
